definition.value: This is an AE which is a type of hematoma of eyelid tissue,the most common cause being capillaries damaged by trauma, causing localized bleeding that extravasates into the surrounding interstitial tissues.
This is an AE which an eye disease.

This is an AE which is a localized bleeding outside of eyelid blood vessels, due to either disease or trauma including injury or surgery and may involve blood continuing to seep from broken capillaries.
This is an AE which is a thin fold of skin that covers and protects an eye and  the skin is susceptible to infection.
This is an AE which is a thin fold of skin that covers and protects an eye and its is injury.
This is an AE which is a state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or eyelid cell-lining damage.
This is an AE which is a brief, involuntary, irregular (lacking rhythm) twitching (different from clonus, which is rhythmic/ regular) of a muscle or a group of muscles and its occurs on eyelid.
This is an AE which is a distressing feeling often caused by intense or damaging stimuli and its occurs on eyelid.
This is an AE which presents within the first year of life either in isolation or as a part of many different ocular or systemic disorders.
This is an AE which is usually secondary to thyroid disorders, trauma, proptosis, seventh nerve palsy, or neurological abnormalities affecting the third nerve.
This is an AE which is a sensation that causes the desire or reflex to scratch on the eyelids.
This is an AE which is a cosmetic problem that results in an older and unnatural appearance.
This is an AE which is a group of eye diseases which result in damage to the optic nerve (or retina) and cause vision loss with traumatic.

This is an AE which is the coordinated control of eye movement with hand movement and the processing of visual input to guide reaching and grasping along with the use of proprioception of the hands to guide the eyes.
This is an AE which is a form of ophthalmic caused by recurrent herpes simplex virus (HSV) infection in the cornea.
This is an AE which occurs due to reactivation of the varicella zoster virus in the ophthalmic branch of the fifth cranial nerve.
This is an AE which is an eye condition in which the directions that the eyes are pointing at rest position, when not performing binocular fusion, are not the same as each other, or, "not straight".
This is an AE which is a medical condition involving inflammatory cells in the anterior chamber of the eye.
This is an AE which is an infrequent, yet potentially vision-threatening, entity.
This is an AE which is the inability to close the eyelids completely.
This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged lacrimal blood vessels.
This is an AE which is a developmental disorder of the eye in which one (unilateral microphthalmia) or both (bilateral microphthalmia) eyes are abnormally small and have anatomic malformations.
This is an AE which is a condition of involuntary (or voluntary, in some cases) eye movement.
This is an AE which may be objectively quantifiable, independent of subjective expressions.
This is an AE which is a form of dysmetria that involves the constant under- or over-shooting of the eyes when attempting to focus gaze on something.
This is an AE which is the presence of elevated fluid pressure inside the eye (intraocular pressure), usually with no optic nerve damage or visual field loss.
This is an AE which is a disorder of ocular function that occurs subsequent to the stenosis of the carotid artery.
This is an AE which is a form of myasthenia gravis in which weakness is restricted to the ocular muscles and may produce significant visual disability.
This is an AE which can affect all parts of the eye, and can be a benign tumor or a malignant tumor (cancer).

This is an AE which is a potentially blinding consequence of craniofacial trauma, but timely ophthalmic evaluation is difficult to obtain in some settings and clear standards for canthotomy/cantholysis are lacking.
This is an AE which is a manifestation of rosacea that affects the eyes and eyelids.
This is an AE which constitute the most common cause of visual disability.

This is an AE which is the inflammation of blood vessels that leads to loss of perfusion and ischemia with necrosis and when this occurs in the orbit, the consequences are typically very conspicuous and can be devastating with decreased quality of life and loss of vision.
This is an AE which is a loss of motor function in one or more muscles of oculofacial.
This is an AE which is characterized by keratoconjunctivitis sicca and by scarring, fibrosis, metaplasia, and shrinkage of the conjunctiva.
This is an AE which is a usually transient condition characterized by bilateral conjunctivitis, facial edema, and upper respiratory symptoms following influenza immunization.
This is an AE which is a form of conjunctivitis (inflammation of the outer eye) which affects newborn babies following birth.
This is an AE which is the formation of a blood clot inside a ophthalmic artery  blood vessel, obstructing the flow of blood through the circulatory system.
This is an AE which is a viral ophthalmic infection caused by the herpes simplex virus .
This is an AE which is shingles involving the eye or the surrounding area.
This is an AE which is a rare neurological disorder of unknown cause which appears to be the result of an autoimmune process involving the nervous system.
This is an AE which is a collection of cranial nerve deficits associated with a mass lesion near the apex of the orbit of the eye.
This is an AE which is the invasion of orbital tissue by disease-causing agents, their multiplication, and the reaction of host tissues to the infectious agents and the toxins they produce.

This is an AE which typically occurs in an idiopathic acute form, with painful diplopia due to inflammation in 1 or more extraocular muscles of young adult females, which usually responds to a course of oral corticosteroids.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the orbital  tissue.
This is an AE which is the inflammation of all coats of the animal eye including intraocular structures.
This is an AE which is the inability to close the eyelids completely with paralytic feel.
This is an AE which is the appearance of swelling in the tissues around the eyes, called the orbits.
This is an AE which is a group of eye diseases which result in damage to the optic nerve (or retina[5]) and cause vision loss.
This is an AE which is an eye condition that manifests through non-specific symptoms such as fatigue, pain in or around the eyes, blurred vision, headache, and occasional double vision.
